1449:../SSC/Src/ecatslv.c **** 
1450:../SSC/Src/ecatslv.c ****  \brief    This function handles the EtherCAT State Machine. It is called
1451:../SSC/Src/ecatslv.c ****             * in case of an AL Control event (Bit 0 of AL-Event (Reg 0x220),
1452:../SSC/Src/ecatslv.c ****                when the Master has written the AL Control Register (from ECAT_Main),
1453:../SSC/Src/ecatslv.c ****               alControl contains the content of the AL Control (Reg 0x120)
1454:../SSC/Src/ecatslv.c ****             * in case of a SM-Change event (Bit 4 of AL-Event (Reg 0x220)),
1455:../SSC/Src/ecatslv.c ****               when an Activate SYNCM y register is written by the master (from ECAT_Main),
1456:../SSC/Src/ecatslv.c ****               alControl contains the actual state (Bit 0-3 of AL Status (Reg 0x130))
1457:../SSC/Src/ecatslv.c ****             * in case of a locally expired watchdog (from ECAT_Main),
1458:../SSC/Src/ecatslv.c ****               alControl contains the requested new state (SAFE_OP)
1459:../SSC/Src/ecatslv.c ****             * in case of an application specific event to change the EtherCAT state (from applicati
1460:../SSC/Src/ecatslv.c ****               alControl contains the requested new state (INIT, PRE_OP or SAFE_OP)
1461:../SSC/Src/ecatslv.c **** 
